Bolivia 1990

*Apertura
*========
*
*First Stage:
*
*Serie A
*
* 1. Bolívar                   12   8  2  2  33-15  20  [La Paz]
* 2. Oriente Petrolero         14   7  4  3  16-18  18  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
* 3. San José                  12   5  4  3  19-12  16  [Oruro]
* 4. Jorge Wilstermann         14   7  0  7  21-21  14  [Cochabamba]
* 5. Ciclón                    14   5  1  8  17-25  11  [Tarija]
* 6. Real Santa Cruz           14   3  4  7  10-23  10  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
*
*[Bolívar and San José received two extra points for not
* having an inter-series rival]
*
*Serie B
*
* 1. The Strongest             12   5  3  4  23-16  13  [La Paz]
* 2. Blooming                  12   4  5  3  21-20  13  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
* 3. Independiente Petrolero   12   6  1  5  13-13  13  [Sucre]
* 4. Destroyers                12   3  4  5  17-27  10  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
* 5. San Pedro                 12   2  2  8  13-13   6  [Cochabamba]
*
*Top-4 of each series qualified for Apertura Second Stage.
*
*Litoral and Always Ready (both La Paz) did not participate in the Apertura.
*
*Top-8 qualified for Apertura Second Stage.
*
*Second Stage
*
*Serie A
*
* 1. Bolívar                    6   4  1  1  15- 3   9  [La Paz]
* 2. Oriente Petrolero          6   3  1  2   8- 5   7  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
* 3. Independiente Petrolero    6   1  3  2   5-11   5  [Sucre]
* 4. Destroyers                 6   1  1  4   2-11   3  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
*
*Serie B
*
* 1. San José                   6   4  0  2   5- 3   8  [Oruro]
* 2. Blooming                   6   3  1  2   6- 5   7  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
* 3. The Strongest              6   3  0  3   6- 5   6  [La Paz]
* 4. Jorge Wilstermann          6   1  1  4   3- 7   3  [Cochabamba]

Round: Semifinals
Bolívar            2-1 0-1 Blooming    
San José           1-1 0-2 Oriente Petrolero        

Round: Final [Oct 28, 31]
Oriente Petrolero  2-1 0-2 Bolívar 

Round: Final Playoff [Nov 4, Cochabamba]
Oriente Petrolero  1-0 Bolívar 


*Clausura
*========
*
*First Stage:
*
*[teams had bonus points; unclear from where]
*
*Serie A [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
*
* 1. Oriente Petrolero          6   3  2  1  10- 6  10 
* 2. Blooming                   6   1  5  0   8- 6   9 
* 3. Real Santa Cruz            6   2  2  2   6- 7   7 
* 4. Destroyers                 6   0  3  3   5-10   5
*
*Top-3 qualified for Clausura second stage.
*
*Serie B [La Paz]
*
* 1. The Strongest              6   5  1  0  10- 0  13 
* 2. Bolívar                    6   3  1  2  14- 5   9
* 3. Litoral                    6   1  1  4   2-11   3
* 4. Always Ready               6   1  1  4   3-13   3
*
*Top-2 qualified for Clausura second stage.
*
*Serie C [other cities]
*
* 1. Ciclón                     8   4  3  1  11- 7  12  [Tarija]
* 2. San José                   8   3  2  3  12-11  10  [Oruro]
* 3. Independiente Petrolero    8   3  2  3  11-11  10  [Sucre]
* 4. Jorge Wilstermann          8   2  4  2  10-10  10  [Cochabamba]
* 5. San Pedro                  8   2  1  5   5-10   6  [Cochabamba]
*
*Top-3 qualified for Clausura second stage.
*
*Second Stage:
*
*Serie A
*
* 1. Bolívar                    6   2  4  0   9- 4   8  [La Paz]
* 2. San José                   6   2  3  1   9- 5   7  [Oruro]
* 3. Real Santa Cruz            6   1  3  2   9-13   5  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
* 4. Blooming                   6   1  2  3   5-10   4  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
*
*Serie B
*
* 1. Oriente Petrolero          6   4  1  1  12- 6   9  [Santa Cruz de la Sierra]
* 2. The Strongest              6   2  3  1  10-10   7  [La Paz] 
* 3. Independiente Petrolero    6   2  1  3   8- 9   5  [Sucre]
* 4. Ciclón                     6   1  1  4   7-12   3  [Tarija]

Semifinals
Bolívar            2-1 4-3 The Strongest
Oriente Petrolero  3-0 0-3 San José  

Final 
Bolívar            4-1 1-2 Oriente Petrolero

Final Playoff [Cochabamba]
Oriente Petrolero  1-1 Bolívar 
Oriente Petrolero won 4-3 on penalties

Oriente Petrolero won Clausura 1990.

As winners of both Apertura and Clausura, Oriente Petrolero are champions
of Bolivia 1990.

As runners-up in both tournaments, Bolívar qualify for Copa
Libertadores 1991 along with Oriente Petrolero.

Promoted: Orcobol (Cochabamba), Petrolero (Cochabamba) and
          Chaco Petrolero (La Paz).
Relegated: San Pedro (Cochabamba) and Litoral (La Paz).

